"Once blogs are featured on the cover of business magazines, it's safe to say they are mainstream. In the enterprise, blogs are used for public relations, work sharing, and even to generate advertising revenue. Hosted blog services are proliferating. If you are asked to host a blog in-house, without a budget, and without committing to one technical direction or platform, you will probably turn to open-source software. Open-source blogs and content management systems are similar in structure, and pose similar security considerations, summarized here."
